<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-465-642  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 465 642.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  June 1990 v3 n6 p64(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Spell-checking moves beyond mere word processing. (SoftwareReview) (Geller Software Laboratories SpellCode)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Falkner, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Geller Software Laboratories Inc. (products).andO;Product:   SpellCode (Word processing software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Utility ProgramsSpelling CheckersEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Spell-Checking Moves Beyond Mere Word Processing Spelling errors are just asembarrassing on a spreadsheet or database as they are on a written report.andO;Until now, however, most spell-checkers have worked only with wordprocessors; users of other types of applications have been on their own.andM;With SpellCode, from Geller Software, your spreadsheet files, databasefields, and code files can be as error-free as your word processingdocuments.andP;  The fast-working program includes a large English-languagedictionary and auxiliary dictionaries for programming languages.andM;SpellCode checks for errors in label cells in Lotus 1-2-3--compatiblespreadsheets, fields (including memo fields) in dBASE-compatible databases,and text that you'll display with C, Pascal, BASIC, PAL, R:Base, and severaldBASE-compatible languages.andP;  It also looks for misspellings in binary andASCII files, Paradox databases, FoxPro memo fields, and 1-2-3 Release 3spreadsheets.andM;The simple user interface almost eliminates the need for SpellCode's briefmanual.andP;  The screen is divided into an upper section for viewing errors and alower area for selecting files and spell-check options.andP;  You use functionkeys to display directories, to select the file type you want to check(dBASE, 1-2-3, and so on), and to choose other options.andM;If you need to check a lot of files, use wildcards to select and review themall at once.andP;  Once the spell-check begins, SpellCode displays suspectederrors at the top of the screen and suggests alternate spellings at thebottom.andP;  You can replace the questionable word with an alternate, skip overit once or every time it occurs, add words to a personal dictionary, andreport errors to screen, printer, or disk.andM;SpellCode does have some limitations.andP;  When checking spreadsheets, it reportserrors for abbreviated column headings or custom macros.andP;  With programminglanguages, SpellCode reports most variable names as errors.andP;  Unless you storethose variables in an auxiliary dictionary, the spell-check can becometedious.andM;All in all, though, SpellCode is a great quality-control tool thatsignificantly extends the reach of an important PC function.andO;</TEXT></DOC>